n\nFaster dedupe, but now we maintain another index and need to think about partial-write consistency.\n\n```text\nOption C: store each record by hash\n:transcript:<hash> = envelope_json\n```\n\nEasy dedupe, worse ordering, more keys, less log-like.\n\nSo my take: current shape is the most reasonable small POC shape. If we later see large-session performance pain, the clean next step would be adding a transcript hash index. I would not add it yet.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-09T16:48:10.514Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}